                            <comment id="463601" author="hornc" created="Mon, 14 Jul 2025 15:53:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;AFAIK, yes that should still be the case today.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="462444" author="adilger" created="Thu, 3 Jul 2025 22:04:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;One of the questions that I always have with the new LNet configuration code is whether a single YAML config file can be used to configure &lt;b&gt;all&lt;/b&gt; of the nodes in a system, or if the lnet.conf file needs to be customized for each client/server?  In the old days (module parameters), using &quot;&lt;tt&gt;ip2nets&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; allowed configuring all clients with multiple network interface types using a single configuration file that is part of the client image.  Is that still the case today?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
